00:13:52,031 --> 00:13:53,900
What happened?

286
00:13:53,900 --> 00:13:54,934
Jill!

287
00:13:54,934 --> 00:13:56,769
I thought you'd gone!

288
00:13:56,769 --> 00:13:59,439
I told the others to leave.

289
00:13:59,439 --> 00:14:00,973
She looks bad!

290
00:14:00,973 --> 00:14:02,742
Bring her to my house!

291
00:14:02,742 --> 00:14:05,478
♪

292
00:14:05,478 --> 00:14:07,613
(laughing)

293
00:14:07,613 --> 00:14:10,183
♪

294
00:14:10,183 --> 00:14:15,188
Master, our Baddies
army has wonderful news!

295
00:14:15,188 --> 00:14:16,689
Victory!

296
00:14:16,689 --> 00:14:18,291
Victory!

297
00:14:18,291 --> 00:14:20,426
(growling)

298
00:14:20,426 --> 00:14:29,969
♪

299
00:14:29,969 --> 00:14:32,105
What's going on?

300
00:14:32,105 --> 00:14:37,310
♪

301
00:14:37,310 --> 00:14:38,544
Master Moo!

302
00:14:38,544 --> 00:14:40,146
Something's wrong with him.

303
00:14:40,146 --> 00:14:41,581
Prepare to fire!

304
00:14:46,319 --> 00:14:47,487
Fire!

305
00:14:47,487 --> 00:14:49,155
(lasers firing)

306
00:14:49,155 --> 00:14:55,128
♪

307
00:14:55,128 --> 00:14:58,164
Fall back!

308
00:14:58,164 --> 00:15:04,370
♪

309
00:15:04,370 --> 00:15:07,039
(roaring)

310
00:15:07,039 --> 00:15:28,961
♪

311
00:15:28,961 --> 00:15:30,763
(laughing)

312
00:15:30,763 --> 00:15:32,598
What's that?

313
00:15:32,598 --> 00:15:35,535
It sounded like Moo again!

314
00:15:35,535 --> 00:15:37,437
(panting)

315
00:15:39,605 --> 00:15:42,542
All right, we're taking
off for Mount Kyrus.

316
00:15:42,542 --> 00:15:43,776
Keep us posted!

317
00:15:43,776 --> 00:15:45,044
If the final gate is there,

318
00:15:45,044 --> 00:15:47,847
we might be able to
resurrect the Phoenix!

319
00:15:47,847 --> 00:15:50,016
You sure you'll be all right?

320
00:15:50,016 --> 00:15:53,719
My troops are pirate dragons,
so we'll make out okay.

321
00:15:53,719 --> 00:15:55,021
Move out!

322
00:15:55,021 --> 00:15:59,659
♪

323
00:15:59,659 --> 00:16:03,696
I'm afraid Pixie might
become a lost disk.

324
00:16:03,696 --> 00:16:05,398
Poor Pixie.

325
00:16:06,999 --> 00:16:09,302
Is there a shrine nearby here?

326
00:16:09,302 --> 00:16:11,938
Well, yes, there is!

327
00:16:11,938 --> 00:16:13,706
Then take us there.

328
00:16:13,706 --> 00:16:16,843
Don't tell me‐‐Pixie!

329
00:16:16,843 --> 00:16:19,645
Think twice about
this, Big Blue!

330
00:16:19,645 --> 00:16:21,547
Don't do it, 'chi!

331
00:16:21,547 --> 00:16:23,950
They're right!

332
00:16:23,950 --> 00:16:25,618
No, Big Blue.

333
00:16:25,618 --> 00:16:26,786
What is it?

334
00:16:26,786 --> 00:16:30,156
Big Blue wants to fuse with
Pixie in order to save her!

335
00:16:30,156 --> 00:16:31,424
Are you serious?

336
00:16:31,424 --> 00:16:35,127
But if he does that, Big
Blue might cease to exist!

337
00:16:35,127 --> 00:16:36,596
'chi!

338
00:16:36,596 --> 00:16:39,398
That'd be the same as
becoming a lost disk!

339
00:16:39,398 --> 00:16:41,067
Fusing no good!

340
00:16:41,067 --> 00:16:43,135
I won't be a lost disk.

341
00:16:43,135 --> 00:16:46,038
I'll continue to
exist inside of Pixie,

342
00:16:46,038 --> 00:16:49,575
and that's good enough for
me if it means Pixie can live.

343
00:16:49,575 --> 00:16:52,011
"Good enough?"

344
00:16:52,011 --> 00:16:53,479
'chi.

345
00:16:53,479 --> 00:16:57,583
♪

346
00:16:57,583 --> 00:16:59,519
(whimpering)

347
00:16:59,519 --> 00:17:01,521
♪

348
00:17:01,521 --> 00:17:03,823
Don't do it.

349
00:17:03,823 --> 00:17:06,425
‐I am ready.
‐You're sure now?

350
00:17:06,425 --> 00:17:08,127
Because in all probability,

351
00:17:08,127 --> 00:17:10,796
you're going to cease to exist!

352
00:17:10,796 --> 00:17:13,900
‐Are you sure about this?
‐Mmm.

353
00:17:13,900 --> 00:17:15,968
♪

354
00:17:15,968 --> 00:17:17,570
'chi.

355
00:17:17,570 --> 00:17:19,171
We're gonna miss you!

356
00:17:19,171 --> 00:17:20,606
You mean a lot to us.

357
00:17:20,606 --> 00:17:22,475
You're a great friend!

358
00:17:22,475 --> 00:17:25,411
Golem will miss you!

359
00:17:25,411 --> 00:17:27,613
No, Big Blue!

360
00:17:30,783 --> 00:17:33,352
(crying)

361
00:17:33,352 --> 00:17:41,027
♪

362
00:17:41,027 --> 00:17:42,328
Huh?

363
00:17:42,328 --> 00:17:43,829
I'm crying!

364
00:17:43,829 --> 00:17:47,867
I thought I'd
forgotten how to cry.

365
00:17:47,867 --> 00:17:50,269
(panting)

366
00:17:50,269 --> 00:17:52,538
♪

367
00:17:52,538 --> 00:17:54,240
It's time.

368
00:17:54,240 --> 00:18:12,091
♪

369
00:18:12,091 --> 00:18:15,294
I'll never forget any of you.

370
00:18:15,294 --> 00:18:18,497
(whimpering)

371
00:18:18,497 --> 00:18:20,466
(together)
Unlock!

372
00:18:20,466 --> 00:18:24,937
♪

373
00:18:24,937 --> 00:18:27,506
Thank you, my dear friends.

374
00:18:27,506 --> 00:18:55,701
♪

375
00:18:55,701 --> 00:18:57,937
(gasping)

376
00:18:57,937 --> 00:19:00,573
♪

377
00:19:00,573 --> 00:19:02,308
Granity.

378
00:19:02,308 --> 00:19:13,419
♪

379
00:19:13,419 --> 00:19:16,322
It's you.

380
00:19:16,322 --> 00:19:17,456
What's this?

381
00:19:17,456 --> 00:19:19,225
Something's happened
and changed my body,

382
00:19:19,225 --> 00:19:23,529
but that can't happen
unless someone fuses‐‐

383
00:19:23,529 --> 00:19:25,865
(gasping)

384
00:19:25,865 --> 00:19:27,366
Where's Big Blue?

385
00:19:27,366 --> 00:19:28,868
Where did Big Blue go?

386
00:19:28,868 --> 00:19:32,038
I think you know what happened.

387
00:19:32,038 --> 00:19:36,742
Big Blue fused with you in
order to save your life, Pixie.

388
00:19:36,742 --> 00:19:37,843
He what?

389
00:19:37,843 --> 00:19:39,845
How could he
throw away his life?

390
00:19:39,845 --> 00:19:42,081
You've got it all wrong.

391
00:19:42,081 --> 00:19:45,718
Big Blue lives inside Granity!

392
00:19:45,718 --> 00:19:49,221
He said that was good
enough if it would save you.

393
00:19:49,221 --> 00:19:52,291
And also he thanked us.

394
00:19:52,291 --> 00:19:55,761
♪

395
00:19:55,761 --> 00:19:58,431
Oh, Big Blue.

396
00:19:58,431 --> 00:20:00,933
Where's the Baddies' crest?

397
00:20:00,933 --> 00:20:03,335
Two life forms
have fused together.

398
00:20:03,335 --> 00:20:05,671
You've become a new life form.

399
00:20:05,671 --> 00:20:09,308
Fused to become a new life form.

400
00:20:09,308 --> 00:20:12,845
The Phoenix's soul may have
been reborn into a monster,

401
00:20:12,845 --> 00:20:15,614
but the monster
doesn't realize it.

402
00:20:15,614 --> 00:20:17,516
♪

403
00:20:17,516 --> 00:20:19,218
If that's possible,

404
00:20:19,218 --> 00:20:22,354
if the body the Phoenix's
soul possesses is fused,

405
00:20:22,354 --> 00:20:24,490
then wouldn't the
Phoenix be reborn?

406
00:20:24,490 --> 00:20:26,592
You'd better get
away from here, Jill.

407
00:20:26,592 --> 00:20:30,463
We'll wait with the Phoenix
until Vulcan returns.

408
00:20:30,463 --> 00:20:32,098
Is it possible?

409
00:20:32,098 --> 00:20:33,699
Could it be?

410
00:20:33,699 --> 00:20:37,169
♪

411
00:20:37,169 --> 00:20:40,439
(roaring)

412
00:20:40,439 --> 00:20:42,775
(evil laughter)

413
00:20:42,775 --> 00:20:47,513
♪

414
00:20:47,513 --> 00:20:48,647
♪ Monsters ♪

415
00:20:48,647 --> 00:20:50,216
♪ Monsters rule ♪

416
00:20:50,216 --> 00:21:14,907
♪

417
00:21:14,907 --> 00:21:16,442
♪ Monsters rule ♪

